snippet.textDisplay:
I'm scared. I'm fucking terrified, not even kidding about this shit.

Ok, so, I dreamt I was lost, trying to find my way walking in the woods at night. It was dark, but I had my cellphone with me so I could see enough. (If it was irl I would be freaking out about draining my battery and losing my flashlight/cellphone)

I was (surprisingly, given the situation) chill. When Lakeith Stanfield showed up like "Yo, are you lost?" and I'm like "yeah, dude, I'm lost".

And he's like giving me a Pity-ful look while saying "that sucks. So, I'm going to this Party and I can take you with me if you want" and I'm like "fuck yeah, take me!"

Don't do that, kids. I know Lakeith's probably an angel, but still.
Unless you're alone in the woods at night, where evil people can find you or wolves can eat you, then go with Lakeith and don't think twice.

Anyways, we arrived. (I have no memories of the travel, just before and after and I'm pissed). The party was awesome.

There were lots of people playing Bendy And The Ink Machine on the wall. Not in a TV or any screens of any sorts, just at the wall. Amoung all that crowd of unknown people I saw Donald Glover (I watched too much Atlanta)

But now comes the important part:

While in the party, checking my phone, I received a notification from the Crybabies Amino, saying "new Unreleased song found!!" or something.

Then I opened it and it was a beautiful song, really similar to that mysterious "Paper People" snippet that got released a while ago after K-12 was annouced that most people believe it's fake. I don't really have an opinion on that tho.

I remember the Internet became a huge discussion because, at a certain point, some people heard the word "bad" and some heard the word "blue". Kinda like a Laurel/Yanny scenario but Melanie themed.

I don't really remember the context, but I do remember it was extraordinarily impossible to tell, and it was one of those things you'd hear what you read or thought and each time it sounded different.

Then I woke up. Ate my breakfast. Everything was normal, until........

I got my cellphone and read a notification from Crybabies Amino saying "New Melanie song!!!!"

And I'm like "bitch, this a fucking clickbait, it can't be!!"

And it was. Copycat. A new Melanie song. Out of the fucking blue. With no annoucement. Brilliant. First collab. With rap.

And I predicted it.

That's pretty much it, good night, ladies and gentlemen.
